==English==

===Etymology===
{{blend|sheep|people}}; first used in [[Google]]'s [[Usenet]] archive on 26 September 1991 in an article on soc.culture.african.american<!--the following is not relevant either to the etymology nor to the article:  A [[CD]] titled "We the Sheeple" was released 11 February 1994 by [[w:TVTV$|TVTV$]].-->...though some attribute it to earlier writings by Anton LaVey, founder of the Church of Satan, who was evidently somewhat prone to using the term.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[sheople]]<!-- about 200 Google hits compared to 26,000 for "sheeple" -->

===Noun===
'''sheeple''' ''plural'' (''no singular'')
#(''derogatory slang'') People who [[unquestioningly]] accept as true whatever their political leaders say or who adopt popular opinion as their own without [[scrutiny]].
#:''The American sheeple should know that George W. Bush is not really for smaller government.''
#:''The 'sheeple' of Toronto have spoken and Ontario gets another coat of red paint''.

